00:00:06,899 --> 00:00:08,851
<i>KIM: Security will escort you out.</i>

5
00:00:08,853 --> 00:00:10,492
<i>MINA: If my sister has a child,</i>

6
00:00:10,494 --> 00:00:12,160
then that child becomes my family, too.

7
00:00:12,162 --> 00:00:14,029
Are you saying you'll
be my baby's godmother?

8
00:00:14,031 --> 00:00:16,054
<i>AUSTIN: You said yes?</i>
All right, so what's your plan

9
00:00:16,056 --> 00:00:18,011
if Adaku's baby becomes
your responsibility?

10
00:00:18,013 --> 00:00:19,093
I don't have one.

11
00:00:19,095 --> 00:00:22,561
<i>There was a learning
curve, but I mastered it.</i>

12
00:00:22,563 --> 00:00:24,357
Why don't you come
over to our place later?

13
00:00:24,359 --> 00:00:26,218
Uh, not tonight.

14
00:00:26,220 --> 00:00:27,526
<i>I'm tired.</i>

15
00:00:27,528 --> 00:00:30,029
<i>A little time alone with my thoughts.</i>

16
00:00:37,304 --> 00:00:40,186
<i>CONRAD: This incredible woman
had the ability to save a life</i>

17
00:00:40,188 --> 00:00:42,433
<i>right in front of me. And
I knew, in that moment,</i>

18
00:00:42,435 --> 00:00:43,876
<i>that I wanted to be a person</i>

19
00:00:43,878 --> 00:00:47,547
<i>who could jump out of
the car to help people.</i>

20
00:00:47,549 --> 00:00:49,483
<i>So that's what I do.</i>

21
00:00:56,149 --> 00:00:57,866
(EXHALES)

22
00:01:01,729 --> 00:01:04,397
NIC: Methodist Memorial
went with someone else.

23
00:01:04,399 --> 00:01:08,401
(SIGHS) Apparently they checked
in with my last employer.

24
00:01:08,403 --> 00:01:10,001
Red Rock has gotten you blacklisted

25
00:01:10,003 --> 00:01:11,682
from every hospital in Atlanta.

26
00:01:11,684 --> 00:01:13,166
I want to practice medicine,

27
00:01:13,168 --> 00:01:15,394
I'll have to find work out of town.

28
00:01:16,354 --> 00:01:18,228
Have a long-distance relationship

29
00:01:18,230 --> 00:01:20,471
or give up being a doctor.
This is what it's come to?

30
00:01:20,473 --> 00:01:21,829
No, it hasn't.

31
00:01:21,831 --> 00:01:24,877
We're gonna figure this out.

32
00:01:24,879 --> 00:01:26,454
You should go, you're gonna be late.

33
00:01:26,456 --> 00:01:28,122
Eh...

34
00:01:28,124 --> 00:01:29,382
(GROANS)

35
00:01:30,115 --> 00:01:31,470
(GRUNTS)

36
00:01:31,472 --> 00:01:33,529
You have any idea why
Reggie wanted to see you?

37
00:01:33,531 --> 00:01:35,670
No, he just said to meet him

38
00:01:35,672 --> 00:01:37,812
at the Georgia FC practice field.

39
00:01:37,814 --> 00:01:40,565
Is it bad that I had no idea
Atlanta has a soccer team?

40
00:01:41,587 --> 00:01:43,137
Yes.

41
00:01:43,139 --> 00:01:44,772
But I forgive you.

42
00:01:50,238 --> 00:01:52,572
(INDISTINCT CHATTER IN BACKGROUND)

43
00:01:52,574 --> 00:01:55,630
Well, hel-hello, good sir.

44
00:01:55,632 --> 00:01:57,450
Some tea and crumpets, perhaps?

45
00:01:57,452 --> 00:01:59,059
Ha. Very funny.

46
00:01:59,061 --> 00:02:01,230
I need to make a good
impression on my new attending.

47
00:02:01,232 --> 00:02:03,833
Ah, right, first day in
the dual residency program.

48
00:02:03,835 --> 00:02:05,449
Internal medicine this week. ER next.

49
00:02:05,451 --> 00:02:07,403
And then I go back and forth.

50
00:02:07,405 --> 00:02:10,789
IRVING: A foot in two
departments fundamentally at odds.

51
00:02:10,791 --> 00:02:13,130
Well, as a dual resident, I
can reach across the aisle,

52
00:02:13,132 --> 00:02:15,098
help each department
see how the other lives.

53
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:16,286
If you say so.

54
00:02:16,288 --> 00:02:18,288
But lose the bow tie.

55
00:02:18,290 --> 00:02:19,766
You look like a chemistry professor

56
00:02:19,768 --> 00:02:21,125
who refuses to hand out As

57
00:02:21,127 --> 00:02:23,129
even when they're totally deserved.

58
00:02:23,131 --> 00:02:25,491
- That was oddly specific.
- I was really good at chemistry.

59
00:02:29,798 --> 00:02:32,057
Fine. You know what?

60
00:02:32,059 --> 00:02:33,651
Okay, baby girl.

61
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:35,927
Your bottle is coming right up.

62
