00:03:11,715 --> 00:03:13,788
- Reggie.
- Dax.

75
00:03:13,790 --> 00:03:16,433
- What's good, Conrad?
- Yeah, good to see you.

76
00:03:16,435 --> 00:03:17,744
- Good to see you.
- Good to see you.

77
00:03:17,746 --> 00:03:20,320
I want you to meet
my mentee, Dax Ramsey.

78
00:03:20,322 --> 00:03:21,684
Yeah, rookie out of Memphis.

79
00:03:21,686 --> 00:03:23,866
You're supposed to be the
next face of the franchise.

80
00:03:23,868 --> 00:03:25,035
Yeah. That's the plan.

81
00:03:25,037 --> 00:03:26,519
If I can get my injuries under control.

82
00:03:26,521 --> 00:03:28,563
Today is Dax's first practice back.

83
00:03:28,565 --> 00:03:31,691
- He's recovering from a calf injury.
- Which feels fine, but...

84
00:03:31,693 --> 00:03:33,932
what worries me is I get
these cramps and injuries

85
00:03:33,934 --> 00:03:34,946
from the smallest things.

86
00:03:34,948 --> 00:03:37,289
The more conditioning I do,
the weaker I seem to get.

87
00:03:37,291 --> 00:03:39,130
The team doc, he ran a bunch of tests.

88
00:03:39,132 --> 00:03:41,882
Everything came back normal,
so he cleared Dax to play.

89
00:03:41,884 --> 00:03:44,037
But I keep telling him
there's something up with me.

90
00:03:44,039 --> 00:03:45,872
But he won't listen, so I asked Reggie

91
00:03:45,874 --> 00:03:47,666
if he knew a doctor who could
give me a second opinion.

92
00:03:47,668 --> 00:03:48,800
And I thought,

93
00:03:48,802 --> 00:03:51,292
why not the guy who
saved my life in zero G?

94
00:03:51,294 --> 00:03:53,028
(LAUGHS)

95
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:55,256
Yeah, well, I'm happy to take
a look at your medical records.

96
00:03:55,258 --> 00:03:58,193
- (WHISTLE BLOWS)
- That's me. Good looking out.

97
00:03:58,195 --> 00:04:00,088
I'll let you know if I find anything.

98
00:04:02,557 --> 00:04:03,574
Buckle up.

99
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:05,599
This may just be a practice game,

100
00:04:05,601 --> 00:04:08,654
but these boys are
about to put on a show.

101
00:04:08,656 --> 00:04:11,248
Ball. Box.

102
00:04:12,493 --> 00:04:15,419
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

103
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:17,087
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

104
00:04:17,089 --> 00:04:20,281
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

105
00:04:20,283 --> 00:04:21,925
<i>♪ Nah-nah-nah-nah-nah-nah-nah, hey! ♪</i>

106
00:04:21,927 --> 00:04:24,744
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

107
00:04:24,746 --> 00:04:27,170
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la... ♪</i>

108
00:04:27,172 --> 00:04:28,779
His footwork's insane.

109
00:04:28,781 --> 00:04:32,019
That's why Dax is the best
rookie this team's ever had.

110
00:04:39,278 --> 00:04:40,519
I need help.

111
00:04:40,521 --> 00:04:42,404
(GROANING)

112
00:04:45,693 --> 00:04:48,494
All right, I got you, I got you.

113
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,647
- Oh! Aah!
- All right.

114
00:04:52,649 --> 00:04:54,649
Your ribs are fractured
in several places.

115
00:04:54,651 --> 00:04:56,627
Your chest wall is unstable.

116
00:04:56,629 --> 00:05:00,113
- We need to get Dax to a hospital.
- REGGIE: I'll call 911.

117
00:05:00,115 --> 00:05:02,154
♪♪

