00:05:13,312 --> 00:05:14,561
Hang in there.

120
00:05:16,167 --> 00:05:17,598
Trauma Bay 10.

121
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,314
When the paramedics called this in,

122
00:05:19,316 --> 00:05:20,625
I wouldn't have guessed
you were with them.

123
00:05:20,627 --> 00:05:22,177
Yeah, trust me, I didn't
expect to be here either.

124
00:05:22,179 --> 00:05:23,821
- Who's the trauma surgeon on today?
- Bell.

125
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:26,413
- He's already on his way.
- Correction. He's already here.

126
00:05:26,415 --> 00:05:28,475
Hawkins, you care to explain
how you ended up here,

127
00:05:28,477 --> 00:05:29,851
yet again, with a patient?

128
00:05:29,853 --> 00:05:31,995
I was at the practice
center when Dax got injured.

129
00:05:31,997 --> 00:05:33,795
- All right, what do we have?
- 19-year-old male,

130
00:05:33,797 --> 00:05:35,431
blunt trauma to the chest and abdomen.

131
00:05:35,433 --> 00:05:38,001
Hypotensive and tachycardic en route.

132
00:05:38,003 --> 00:05:39,319
(DAX GROANS)

133
00:05:39,321 --> 00:05:41,184
I'm Dr. Feldman, this is Dr. Bell.

134
00:05:41,186 --> 00:05:42,247
Do you have any allergies

135
00:05:42,249 --> 00:05:43,490
to any medications we should know about?

136
00:05:43,492 --> 00:05:44,508
Not that I know of.

137
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,376
Nice as it is to see you, Conrad,

138
00:05:46,378 --> 00:05:48,661
- Logan Kim isn't going to like that you're here.
- I know.

139
00:05:48,663 --> 00:05:50,879
I can't just leave him
while he's still in pain.

140
00:05:50,881 --> 00:05:51,988
Hey, Conrad?

141
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:54,478
Yeah, I'm here. We're
gonna take care of you.

142
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,985
I'm a friend of the patient,

143
00:05:55,987 --> 00:05:58,004
that's not against hospital policy.

144
00:05:58,006 --> 00:06:00,858
- (GROANS)
- (ALARM BEEPING)

145
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:03,702
Okay, his O2 stats are dropping.
We need to intubate him.

146
00:06:05,308 --> 00:06:08,167
- Chest cavity is full of blood.
- Get me a chest tube kit.

147
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:10,425
Now, as the friend of the patient,

148
00:06:10,427 --> 00:06:12,550
I'm gonna have to ask you to
step outside the trauma bay.

149
00:06:12,552 --> 00:06:14,279
- That is hospital policy.
- I understand.

150
00:06:14,281 --> 00:06:16,457
I'm playing by the rules on this one.

151
00:06:24,407 --> 00:06:27,367
<i>MAN (OVER P.A.): Dr. Lee
to Infectious Disease.</i>

152
00:06:27,369 --> 00:06:29,303
(PHONE RINGING)

153
00:06:30,829 --> 00:06:32,427
Hey, Dad. I was just on my way out.

154
00:06:32,429 --> 00:06:33,913
Where are you? I'll pick you up.

155
00:06:35,877 --> 00:06:37,511
You're where?

156
00:06:37,513 --> 00:06:39,480
- (SIREN WAILING)
- (INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

157
00:06:42,976 --> 00:06:44,643
It's fine. I'm fine.

158
00:06:44,645 --> 00:06:46,478
You're not fine. You got arrested.

159
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:48,238
You see any handcuffs? I'm okay.

160
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:51,057
Can we just please go?

161
00:06:51,059 --> 00:06:53,577
What the hell happened?
You got into a fight?

162
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:56,464
- It was schoolyard stuff.
- Between two grown men?

163
00:06:56,466 --> 00:06:57,788
Well, he threw the first punch.

164
00:06:57,790 --> 00:06:59,941
The police agree that I'm
innocent, so they released me.

165
00:06:59,943 --> 00:07:02,828
- Who were you fighting?
- This guy, he bought my car.

166
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:05,295
He had buyer's remorse, he
thought I'd take it back.

167
00:07:05,297 --> 00:07:08,241
- And then he made fun of my hat.
- Wait, you-you sold your car?

168
00:07:08,243 --> 00:07:10,618
You've had that car for 20 years.

169
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:12,245
Nic, nothing lasts forever.

170
00:07:12,247 --> 00:07:13,631
Dad.

171
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:17,008
- I'm worried about you.
- (PANTING)

172
00:07:17,010 --> 00:07:20,643
Yes, look... Okay, I've
been a-a little down lately.

173
00:07:20,645 --> 00:07:23,102
But who doesn't hit a rough
patch every now and then?

174
00:07:23,104 --> 00:07:25,438
I'm fine.

175
00:07:26,094 --> 00:07:27,820
I promise.

176
00:07:33,506 --> 00:07:36,029
AUSTIN: Well, the repeat
cultures are negative.

177
00:07:36,031 --> 00:07:37,955
Plus no fever in two days.

178
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:40,815
Which means your infection is clearing.

179
00:07:40,817 --> 00:07:43,484
So I finally get to hold my baby?

180
00:07:43,486 --> 00:07:44,853
Yes, indeed.

181
00:07:44,855 --> 00:07:48,789
However, the results
happen to be so good that...

182
00:07:48,791 --> 00:07:52,377
We can discharge you and send
you home with oral antibiotics.

183
00:07:52,379 --> 00:07:54,287
Yes! Ah...

184
00:07:54,289 --> 00:07:57,832
Thank you both so much for everything.

185
00:07:57,834 --> 00:08:00,491
- You got it.
- I can't wait to have Michelle in my arms

186
00:08:00,493 --> 00:08:02,554
- and finally to be able to get out of here.
- Mm-hmm.

187
00:08:02,556 --> 00:08:04,723
(SIGHS)

188
00:08:04,725 --> 00:08:07,223
Do you think she'll know who I am?

189
00:08:07,225 --> 00:08:09,715
I'm sure she'll know

190
00:08:09,717 --> 00:08:12,155
by the love you give her.

191
00:08:12,157 --> 00:08:13,699
(CHUCKLES)

192
00:08:14,976 --> 00:08:17,327
- ADAKU: Look at how cute she is.
- MINA: Yeah.

193
00:08:17,329 --> 00:08:19,854
(EXHALES)

194
00:08:19,856 --> 00:08:21,147
As my admitting resident,

195
00:08:21,149 --> 00:08:23,333
you are gatekeeper
to the medicine floor.

196
00:08:23,335 --> 00:08:24,576
And when I say "gatekeeper",

197
00:08:24,578 --> 00:08:27,057
I mean you are to be a blocking machine.

198
00:08:27,059 --> 00:08:30,663
Mrs. Allen, 68-year-old female
with alcoholic pancreatitis.

199
00:08:30,665 --> 00:08:32,006
Know what went wrong here?

200
00:08:32,008 --> 00:08:34,483
She binged on alcohol and
gave herself pancreatitis?

201
00:08:34,485 --> 00:08:36,884
Wrong. The ER were too
slow giving her a benzo,

202
00:08:36,886 --> 00:08:38,665
so now we're stuck chasing
her withdrawal symptoms.

203
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:40,556
That's not entirely
fair. The ER is always...

204
00:08:40,558 --> 00:08:42,877
Mr. Hopper, 80-year-old man.

205
00:08:42,879 --> 00:08:44,879
Fell in his home, sprained his hip.

206
00:08:44,881 --> 00:08:45,914
Care to guess the mistake?

207
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:48,600
He's an elderly man who lives alone

208
00:08:48,602 --> 00:08:51,353
- and he needs discharge planning.
- Which could have been done

209
00:08:51,355 --> 00:08:53,605
while he was waiting in the
ER. Instead, he's taking up

210
00:08:53,607 --> 00:08:55,181
one of our beds,
waiting for a placement.

211
00:08:55,183 --> 00:08:57,200
I could go on, but the trend is clear.

212
00:08:57,202 --> 00:09:00,704
We're accepting patients from
the ER that don't belong here.

213
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:03,231
Look, I agree that these patients

214
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,191
in particular could
have been managed better,

215
00:09:05,193 --> 00:09:08,003
but most of the patients on
this floor do need to be here.

216
00:09:11,625 --> 00:09:15,218
I know you're not a
pure medicine resident,

217
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:18,388
that you've been tainted by
habits you learned in the ER.

218
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:22,559
- I wouldn't say that...
- But you're on this team now.

219
00:09:22,561 --> 00:09:24,353
So, what are you going to be?

220
00:09:26,256 --> 00:09:27,880
A blocking machine.

221
00:09:27,882 --> 00:09:31,318
A blocking... machine.

222
00:09:33,263 --> 00:09:36,198
(BUSY CHATTER)

223
00:09:37,892 --> 00:09:39,576
Dr. Hawkins...

224
00:09:39,578 --> 00:09:43,396
this is Bill Landry,
owner of Georgia FC.

225
00:09:43,398 --> 00:09:45,924
Son, I have a team of top
doctors from St. John's

226
00:09:45,926 --> 00:09:47,123
who take care of my players.

227
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:49,610
I don't know who you are
or why you were on my field.

228
00:09:49,612 --> 00:09:52,255
Why exactly did you poach
a patient from St. John's

229
00:09:52,257 --> 00:09:53,749
- and bring him here?
- That's not what happened.

230
00:09:53,751 --> 00:09:54,758
I don't care.

231
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:57,061
I want Dax transferred to
St. John's immediately.

232
00:09:57,063 --> 00:09:58,929
Well, that would be a bad idea.

233
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:02,415
Dax has sustained significant
injuries to his chest

234
00:10:02,417 --> 00:10:04,843
and his abdomen, leading
to multiple broken ribs,

235
00:10:04,845 --> 00:10:07,295
lung contusions,
lacerations to his spleen.

236
00:10:07,297 --> 00:10:09,255
I trust that, when he stabilizes,

237
00:10:09,257 --> 00:10:11,399
you'll make that transfer
happen as soon as possible.

238
00:10:11,401 --> 00:10:12,592
Y-You have my word.

239
00:10:12,594 --> 00:10:16,245
And I apologize for the
inconvenience. I-I hope...

240
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:22,894
Bill Landry is the
richest man in Georgia,

